A hydroxycalciol that is vitamin D2 in which the hydrogen at position 25 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of 3-methyladipic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the  conjugate base of 4-guanidinobutanoic acid.
An arginine derivative that is arginine substituted by two methyl groups. A "closed" class.

A histidine derivative that is histidine in which one of the hydrogens of the alpha-amino group is substituted by an acetyl group.

A beta-D-glucosiduronic acid that is the ethyl derivative of beta-D-glucuronic acid.

A member of the class of 1-benzothiophenes that is 1-benzothiophene in which the hydrogens at positions 2, 3, and 6 have been replaced by p-hydroxyphenyl, p-[2-(piperidin-1-yl)ethoxy]benzoyl, and hydroxy groups, respectively.
A 4-hydroxy-3-(3-oxo-1-phenylbutyl)-2H-1-benzopyran-2-one that has (R)-configuration (the racemate is warfarin, an anticoagulant drug and rodenticide).
A 4-hydroxy-3-(3-oxo-1-phenylbutyl)-2H-1-benzopyran-2-one that has (S)-configuration (the racemate is warfarin, an anticoagulant drug and rodenticide).
A member of the class of  furans used to treat  peptic ulcer disease (PUD) and gastroesophageal reflux disease.
A ketohexose monophosphate consisting of fructose having a phosphate group located at the 6-position.
A phosphoglycerate obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group and one of the phosphate OH groups of 3-phosphoglyceric acid.
An N(6)-acyl-L-lysine derivative in which the acyl group is specified as gamma-glutamyl.

A member of the class of pyridopyrimidines that is 2-methyl-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-4-one carrying an additional 2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl group at position 2.
A cholesteryl octadecenoate in which the acy group is specified as (11Z)-octadec-11-enoyl.

A butenolide that is furan-2(5H)-one substituted by a phenyl group at position 3 and by a p-(methylsulfonyl)phenyl group at position 4. A selective cyclooxygenase 2 inhibitor, it was used from 1999 to 2004 for the treatment of ostoarthritis, but was withdrawn following concerns about an associated increased risk of heart attack and stroke.
A dpeptide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-pyroglutamine with the amino group of L-glutamine

An N-alkylpyrrolidine that is nicotine in which the methylene hydrogens at position 2 on the pyrrolidine ring have been replaced by an oxo group and the pyridine nitrogen converted into the corresponding N-oxide. A minor metabolite of nicotine.
A member of the class of furoic acids that is 2-furoic acid substituted at position 5 by a hydroxymethyl group.
A steroid sulfate that is 17alpha-hydroxypregnenolone in which the hydroxy hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a sulfo group.
A N-acylglycine obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of propionic acid with the amino group of glycine.
A N-acylglycine obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of butyric acid with the amino group of glycine.
An N-acylglycine in which the acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxybenzoyl.

A racemate consisting of equal parts of (R)- and (S)-salmeterol.   It is a potent and selective beta2-adrenoceptor agonist (EC50 = 5.3 nM). Unlike other beta2 agonists, it binds to the exo-site domain of beta2 receptors, producing a slow onset of action and prolonged activation.
An aryl sulfate that is trans-caffeic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen at position 3 is replaced by a sulfo group. A metabolite from coffee.
